RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'M SO FUNNY dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path coming around the turn and kicked clear in the lane. BURNT MATCH bumped with the horse to her inside and then veered in sharply at the break, was urged up to stalk the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and kept on in the lane. I'M BLEU TOO bumped with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, recovered to duel on the inside through the early going, continued to battle while saving ground around the far turn and weakened in the final furlong. NATIVE DOLL dwelt at the start, trailed ten lengths behind the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and made up some ground in the stretch. SASSY BANKER raced off the pace early, saved ground around the bend and made no bid. HAUTE CHARLOTTE tracked the leaders on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the turn in the two path and faded from there. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE START. UPON REVIEW, IT WAS DETERMINED THAT HORSE THREE, NATIVE DOLL, HAD AN EQUAL AND FAIR BEGINNING AND NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 7 1/2F Turf CR: 78. Maiden Special Weight Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be ru n at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) (Rail at 25 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MONGOLIAN APPLE saved ground around the first turn, led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way racing in the two path around the turn and drew off in the stretch. BRIARTOWN raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the second bend and improved position in the lane. STOMPING MOON saved ground early, chased the leader up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and was outkicked in the lane. PRIDE OF ARGYLE raced at the back of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far turn and passed tiring horses in the stretch. UNSTOPPABLE FORCE hit the gate leaving it, saved ground around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second turn and never threatened. A LOT OF HEAT raced in the three path around the first bend, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn still in the three path and faded from there. FUJIN raced in the three path early, continued up the backstretch off the pace, moved up while racing in the three path around the far bend and flattened out in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOON CONNECTION led the way on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and drew off in the lane. LUCKY MCCOY stumbled leaving the gate, raced off the pace on the inside early, began a bid from the two path coming around the turn and improved position in the stretch. TALE OF TRUTH chased the pace setters between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the bend in the three path and kept on to teh wire. WIND RIVER stalked the frontrunner on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the four path and was outkicked from there. MY KACEJJ raced off the pace on the outside through the early going, saved ground around the turn and showed no kick. RUSSELL trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and made no bid. HOLDENTIGHT tracked the leader on the inside early, saved ground around the bend and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 4 1M 70Y Turf CR: 90. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 30 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000. Minne sota Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile and 70 yards on the main track.) (Rail at 25 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUNAWAY READY raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, began a bid headed into the far bend, raced in the two and three path from there, kicked clear in the lane and just held the win while drifting in mildly in the final furlong. CALZONE bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, raced in the two path early, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, angled in to save ground around the far turn, switched outside to began a bid in upper stretch and gained ground late. LINE TO GAIN saved ground around the first turn, tracked the pace setters on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second turn, raced in tight quarters near the eighth pole, found room and gained ground late from there. YIP YIP KIP veered out and bumped the horse to his outside leaving the gate, pressed the pace from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far bend still in the two path and weakened between horses in the final furlong. SWAMPDRAINER saved ground early, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far turn and faded in the final furlong.

Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KIRA FEVER dueled on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and dug in gamely in the stretch to hold the victory. CHAPARRITA bumped lightly with the horse to her outside at the start, recovered to duel up the backstretch, continued to battle from the three path around the bend and kept on gamely to the wire to narrowly miss. COMPETITIVE SPIRIT raced off the pace on the outside early, navigated the turn from the two path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position from there. GRANDIOSE SUMMER raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening quarter, saved ground around the bend and finished evenly while never threatening. VOODOO FIRE trailed the field up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path and showed no kick. IZE SHARPIE chased the leaders up the backstretch, dropped back while racing in the two path around the turn and continued to fade in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 10500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FORTY STRANGERS chased the leader up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground between horses late to get up for the win. HE'S CONNECTED raced off the pace on the outside early, continued around the turn in the three path, launched a bid in upper stretch and gained ground late. CLASS COMPOUNDS dueled on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to battle from the two path coming around the turn, dug in in the lane and was caught late. JUST BECAUSE raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the three path and improved position in the lane. BLUE PARADISE dueled on the inside early, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and faded in the final furlong. WESTERN CHARM dueled between horses up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and tired in the stretch.

MERLIN'S SISTER raced off the pace on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and was not a factor.
